---
description: Single-line comment above every function and const-arrow
globs: ["**/*.ts", "**/*.tsx", "**/*.rs"]
alwaysApply: false
---

# Function and const-arrow comments

- Every **function** and every **const name = (...) => ...** (including async) must have exactly **one line** above it describing what it does. Place the comment immediately above the declaration.
- Use a single short sentence. Focus on intent or effect, not restating the code.
- Avoid inline comments that merely restate the code or feel generic (e.g. do not write "Gets the value of x" for `getX()`).

**Good:**

```typescript
// Polls the desktop server until it responds or attempts are exhausted.
export const ensureDesktopServerReady = async (): Promise<void> => { ... }
```

```rust
// Spawns the llama sidecar and registers it in app state.
pub fn start_desktop_model_server(app: &AppHandle) -> Result<(), String> { ... }
```

**Bad:**

```typescript
// Gets the desktop server ready.  (too vague / restates name)
// This function waits for the server by polling every 500ms up to 30 times.  (inline-style; keep one line above only)
```
